We've got a functional cluster but most useful applications require some kind of storage,
so in this post we'll setup both Postgres and [Longhorn][] together with a fully featured backup system for good measure.

I was initially planning to split this into three separate posts but eh...

This is the plan:

1. Setup [CloudNativePG][] with backups to ZFS
1. Setup [Longhorn][], again backed up to ZFS
1. Add snapshots, copy them to a secondary ZFS pool and to the cloud

# Postgres on Kubernetes

> just because you can run PostgreSQL on Kubernetes doesn't mean you should
> ^ [Why Running Postgres on Kubernetes Is Still a Bad Idea (And What to Do Instead)][]

Meh, I do what I want.

I agree with [their point][Why Running Postgres on Kubernetes Is Still a Bad Idea (And What to Do Instead)] that it's likely better to rely on a managed Postgres service but this is a Homelab so I can safely disregard any sane advice I don't like.

## CloudNativePG

[CloudNativePG][] is supposedly pretty great though, let's get it setup.

A standard application manifest:

```yaml
apiVersion: argoproj.io/v1alpha1
kind: Application
metadata:
  name: cloudnative-pg
  namespace: argocd
  annotations:
    argocd.argoproj.io/sync-wave: "-1"
  finalizers:
    - resources-finalizer.argocd.argoproj.io
spec:
  project: default
  source:
    repoURL: https://cloudnative-pg.github.io/charts
    chart: cloudnative-pg
    targetRevision: 0.28.0
  destination:
    server: https://kubernetes.default.svc
    namespace: cnpg-system
  syncPolicy:
    syncOptions:
      - CreateNamespace=true
      - ServerSideApply=true
    automated:
      prune: true
      selfHeal: true
```

```yaml
apiVersion: postgresql.cnpg.io/v1
kind: Cluster
metadata:
  name: postgres
  namespace: cnpg-system
  annotations:
    argocd.argoproj.io/sync-wave: "0"
    argocd.argoproj.io/sync-options: SkipDryRunOnMissingResource=true
spec:
  instances: 1
  imageName: ghcr.io/inherent-design/cloudnative-pg-timescaledb:18
  storage:
    storageClass: local-path
    size: 200Gi
  postgresql:
    shared_preload_libraries:
      - timescaledb
  bootstrap:
    initdb: {}
```

```yaml
apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: postgres-ip
  namespace: cnpg-system
  annotations:
    argocd.argoproj.io/sync-wave: "1"
    argocd.argoproj.io/sync-options: SkipDryRunOnMissingResource=true
spec:
  type: ClusterIP
  externalIPs:
    - 10.1.4.50
  selector:
    cnpg.io/cluster: postgres
    role: primary
  ports:
    - port: 5432
      targetPort: 5432
```

