# Local path and postgres

Setup local path

```
kubectl get storageclass
NAME                   PROVISIONER                            RECLAIMPOLICY   VOLUMEBINDINGMODE      ALLOWVOLUMEEXPANSION   AGE
local-path (default)   cluster.local/local-path-provisioner   Delete          WaitForFirstConsumer   true                   7m7s
```

```
# Get password
kubectl get secret postgres-app -n cnpg-system -o jsonpath='{.data.password}' | base64 -d
psql -h 10.1.4.103 -U app
# Or
PGPASSWORD=<password> psql -h 10.1.4.103 -U app
# Or
kubectl exec -n cnpg-system postgres-1 -- psql -U postgres
# Allow app user to create database
kubectl exec -n cnpg-system postgres-1 -- psql -U postgres -c "ALTER USER app CREATEDB;"
# Login
```

## Backups

```
CNPG
  └─► Garage (in-cluster, S3-compatible)
        └─► NFS mount → vault/postgres on Proxmox ZFS
                └─► Sanoid/Syncoid → secondary machine (future)
                └─► Restic/Rclone → Backblaze B2
```

